  <static seed="1426" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/complexFractions10.pg">
    <statement><p>Calculate the following. Use an improper fraction in your answer.</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ \frac{25}{3} }{ \frac{5}{7} } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ \frac{t}{y} }{ \frac{x}{r} } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{35}{3}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{tr}{yx}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><alert>Problem 1</alert></p>
<p>To simplify a complex fraction, we find the common denominator of all fractions. In this case, it is <m>21</m>. We multiply the complex fraction<rsq/>s numerator and denominator by this common denominator, and we have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    
      \amp = \frac{ \frac{25}{3} \cdot 21 }{ \frac{5}{7} \cdot 21 } \\
      \amp = \frac{ 175 }{ 15 } \\
      \amp = {{\frac{35}{3}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Here is a simple way to do fraction multiplication:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{25}{3} \cdot 21 = 21 \div 3 \cdot 25 = 175 }</m></p>
<p><alert>Problem 2</alert></p>
<p>To simplify a complex fraction, we find the common denominator of all fractions. In this case, it is <m>{yr}</m>. We multiply the complex fraction<rsq/>s numerator and denominator by this common denominator, and we have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    
      \amp = \frac{ \frac{t}{y} \cdot {yr} }{ \frac{x}{r} \cdot {yr} } \\
      \amp = {\frac{tr}{yx}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
